%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.2/models-as-a-service.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Terminate
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino<br/>gRPC mTLS
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Limitador as Kuadrant Limitador<br/>gRPC mTLS
    participant Model as Model Backend (KServe)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 1: API Key Authentication for Model Inference

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS
    Gateway->>Authorino: ExtAuth check<br/>gRPC mTLS
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+<br/>(NetworkPolicy restricted)
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Validate API key hash<br/>5432/TCP
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key valid + user/group info
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (key metadata)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+<br/>(NetworkPolicy restricted)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription tier info
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth response<br/>Headers: X-MaaS-Username,<br/>X-MaaS-Group, X-MaaS-Key-Id
    Gateway->>Limitador: Token rate limit check<br/>gRPC mTLS
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Allow/Deny (429 if exceeded)
    Gateway->>Model: Forward inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    Model-->>Gateway: Prediction response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 2: API Key Management

    Client->>Gateway: POST /maas-api/v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer (API key or OpenShift token)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS
    Gateway->>Authorino: ExtAuth check<br/>gRPC mTLS
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: Validate credentials<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Auth result
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Authorized
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: Forward to /maas-api/*<br/>8080/TCP or 8443/TCP
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Create/revoke API key<br/>5432/TCP
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Confirmation
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: API key response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: Controller Reconciliation

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MaaSCtrl as maas-controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    MaaSCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch MaaSAuthPolicy,<br/>MaaSModelRef, MaaSSubscription CRs<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSCtrl: CR change events
    MaaSCtrl->>K8sAPI: Read HTTPRoute, LLMInferenceService<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSCtrl: Resource data
    MaaSCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Kuadrant AuthPolicy<br/>& TokenRateLimitPolicy<br/>HTTPS/443
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSCtrl: Confirmation
